to create amazing things. However, if you are turning a profit from my hard work, it
is only fair that we share the success or keep the open-source ecosystem thriving.

### THE RULES (PERMISSIONS & CONDITIONS)
Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy of this
software and associated documentation files (the "Software"), to deal in the Software
without restriction, subject to the following conditions:

**1. Free for Open & Non-Profit Use:**
You may use, copy, modify, merge, publish, and distribute the Software freely for
personal, educational, or open-source projects where no revenue is generated.

**2. The Commercial Catch:**
If you use this Software, or any modified version of it, in a project intended to
generate revenue (including but not limited to paid software, SaaS, in-app purchases,
or applications running advertisements), **or if you use this Software or any
modified version of it internally within, or on behalf of, a for-profit entity —
whether or not the Software itself is sold, distributed, or exposed to end users** —
you must choose ONE of the following paths:
*   **Option A (Pay It Forward):** You must release the entire source code of your
    revenue-generating (or internally-used) project publicly under an
    **OSI-approved open source license** (see https://opensource.org/licenses for
    the current list). A license not on that list does not satisfy this option.
*   **Option B (Pay the Piper):** You must contact the original author at the
    contact information provided above to negotiate a commercial license, revenue
    cut, or flat fee *before* public launch, internal deployment, or monetization.

**3. Credit Where It's Due (Attribution):**
If any portion of this Software is integrated into your project, you must provide
clear, public credit to the original author. This credit must be easily visible to
end-users and developers (for example, in an "About" page, a "Credits" screen, or
prominently within the project's primary README file). This attribution requirement
does not grant any trademark, branding, or endorsement rights — see "No Trademark
Rights" below.

**4. No Trademark Rights:**
Nothing in this license grants permission to use the original author's name, alias,
or any associated branding to imply endorsement, sponsorship, or affiliation with
your project, beyond the plain attribution required by Section 3.

**5. Termination:**
This license, and all rights granted under it, terminate automatically and
immediately if you fail to comply with Section 2 (The Commercial Catch). Upon
termination, you must cease all use, distribution, and monetization of the Software
and any modified version of it until compliance is restored or a separate agreement
is reached with the original author under Option B.

